<P><B>Software Design Engineer - Req #48615</B></P>
<P>
Is the computer still too difficult to use? Wouldn't it be cool if the computer could understand human languages (whether it was typed or spoken)? Interested in developing cutting edge products that encompass speech recognition, natural language searches and understanding? We are looking for a passionate individual to drive the ever-important computer learning components. Primary responsibilities include working with other groups to apply statistical learning methods for understanding natural language queries and commands (both written and spoken). The candidate will join a high performance team to deliver the component that automatically learns the semantic understanding (matching) from supervised and unsupervised data. In addition, the team will apply learning algorithms for query/document clustering and data mining. Minimum 3 years experience with C/C++ and strong programming skills are required. .NET Framework, C#, XML, and SQL knowledge and experience are a big plus. A BA/BS or MS degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related technical discipline preferred. Candidates must also be able to collaborate effectively with cross-group teams to assure unification across different modalities.
</P>
  


